==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|melancholly}}, {{l|en|melancholie}}, {{l|en|melancholious}} {{lb|en|obsolete}}

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|malencolie}}, from {{der|en|fro|melancolie}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|μελαγχολία||[[atrabiliousness]]}}, from {{m|grc|μέλας|}}, {{m|grc|μελαν-||black, dark, murky}} + {{m|grc|χολή||bile}}. Compare the {{cog|la|ātra bīlis||black bile}}. The adjectival use is a Middle English innovation, perhaps influenced by the suffixes {{m|en|-y}}, {{m|en|-ly}}.

